mention.text: The sufferings of mortality , Seen in their sad reality
things that gods despise ; What was thy pity 's recompense ?
The fate thou didst so well
his own mind ; But baffled as thou wert from high , Still in thy patient energy
A troubled stream from a pure source
his sad unallied existence : To which his Spirit may oppose Itself -- and equal to all woes , And a firm will
